===Time===
{| class=&quot;wikitable&quot;
|+ [[Time]], t
!Name of unit
!Symbol
!Definition
!Relation to SI units
|-
| [[atomic units|atomic unit of time]] || au
| ≡ [[Bohr radius|a&lt;sub&gt;0&lt;/sub&gt;]]/([[fine structure constant|α]]·c)
| ≈ {{nowrap|2.418 884 254{{e|−17}}}} s
|-
| [[Callippic cycle]] || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ 441 mo (hollow) + 499 mo (full) = 76 a of 365.25 d
| = {{nowrap|2.398 3776{{e|9}}}} s
|-
| [[century]] || c
| ≡ 100 a (see below for definition of year length)
| = 100 × year
|-
| [[day]] || d
| = 24 h
| = {{gaps|86|400|u=s}}
|-
| [[day]] (sidereal) || d
| ≡ Time needed for the Earth to rotate once around its axis, determined from successive transits of a very distant astronomical object across an observer's meridian ([[International Celestial Reference Frame]])
| ≈ {{nowrap|86 164.1}} s
|-
| [[decade]] || dec
| ≡ 10 a (see below for definition of year length)
| = 10 × year
|-
| [[fortnight]] || fn
| ≡ 2 wk
| = {{nowrap|1 209 600}} s
|-
| [[helek]] ||
| ≡ {{nowrap|1/1 080}} h
| = 3.{{overline|3}} s
|-
| [[Hipparchic cycle]] || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ 4 Callippic cycles - 1 d
| = {{nowrap|9.593 424{{e|9}}}} s
|-
| [[hour]] || h
| ≡ 60 min
| = {{nowrap|3 600}} s
|-
| [[jiffy (time)|jiffy]] || j
| ≡ 1/60 s
| = .01{{overline|6}} s
|-
| jiffy (alternate) || ja
| ≡ 1/100 s
| = 10 ms
|-
| [[ke (unit)|ke]] (quarter of an hour) || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ ¼ h = 1/96 d
| = 60 × 60 / 4 s = 900 s = 60 / 4 min = 15 min
|-
| [[ke (unit)|ke]] (traditional) || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ 1/100 d
| = 24 × 60 × 60 / 100 s = 864 s = 24 * 60 / 100 min = 14.4 min
|-
| lustre; lustrum || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ 5 a of 365 d
| = 1.5768{{e|8}} s
|-
| [[Metonic cycle]]; enneadecaeteris || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ 110 mo (hollow) + 125 mo (full) = 6940 d ≈ 19 a
| = {{nowrap|5.996 16{{e|8}}}} s
|-
| [[millennium]] || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ {{nowrap|1 000}} a (see below for definition of year length)
| = 1000 × year
|-
| [[Metric time#Alternative units|milliday]] || md
| ≡ 1/{{nowrap|1 000}} d
| = 24 × 60 × 60 / {{nowrap|1 000}} s = 86.4 s
|-
| [[minute]] || min
| ≡ 60 s, due to [[leap second]]s sometimes 59 s or 61 s,
| = 60 s
|-
| [[moment (time)|moment]] || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ 90 s
| = 90 s
|-
| [[month]] (full) || mo
| ≡ 30 d&lt;ref name=&quot;PedersenGloss&quot;&gt;Pedersen O. (1983). &quot;Glossary&quot; in [[George Coyne|Coyne, G.]], Hoskin, M., and Pedersen, O. ''Gregorian Reform of the Calendar: Proceedings of the Vatican Conference to Commemorate its 400th Anniversary''. Vatican Observatory. Available from [[Astrophysics Data System]].&lt;/ref&gt;
| = {{nowrap|2 592 000}} s
|-
| [[month]] (Greg. av.) || mo
| Average Gregorian month = 365.2425/12 d = 30.436875 d
| ≈ {{nowrap|2.6297{{e|6}}}} s
|-
| [[month]] (hollow) || mo
| ≡ 29 d&lt;ref name=&quot;PedersenGloss&quot;/&gt;
| = {{nowrap|2 505 600}} s
|-
| [[month]] (synodic) || mo
| Cycle time of moon phases ≈ 29.530589 days (Average)
| ≈ {{nowrap|2.551{{e|6}}}} s
|-
| [[octaeteris]] || &amp;nbsp;
| = 48 mo (full) + 48 mo (hollow) + 3 mo (full)&lt;ref&gt;{{Citation | last=Richards | first=E.G. | title=Mapping Time | year=1998 | pages=94–95 | publisher=Oxford University Press | isbn=0-19-850413-6}}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;{{Citation | last=Steel | first=Duncan | title=Marking Time | year=2000 | page=46 | publisher=John Wiley &amp; Sons | isbn=0-471-29827-1}}&lt;/ref&gt; = 8 a of 365.25 d = 2922 d
| = {{nowrap|2.524 608{{e|8}}}} s
|-
| [[Planck time]] || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ ([[gravitational constant|G]][[reduced Planck constant|{{Unicode|ℏ}}]]/''[[speed of light|c]]''&lt;sup&gt;5&lt;/sup&gt;)&lt;sup&gt;½&lt;/sup&gt;
| ≈ {{nowrap|1.351 211 868{{e|−43}}}} s
|- style=&quot;background:#dfd;&quot;
| [[second]] || s
| time of {{nowrap|9 192 631 770}} periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the 2 hyperfine levels of the ground state of the caesium 133 atom at 0 K&lt;ref name=&quot;sibaseunits&quot;/&gt; (but other seconds are sometimes used in astronomy)
| ([[SI base unit]])
|-
| [[shake (time)|shake]] || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ 10&lt;sup&gt;−8&lt;/sup&gt; s
| = 10 ns
|-
| sigma || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ 10&lt;sup&gt;−6&lt;/sup&gt; s
| = 1 μs
|-
| [[Sothic cycle]] || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ {{nowrap|1 461}} a of 365 d
| = {{nowrap|4.607 4096{{e|10}}}} s
|-
| [[svedberg]] || S
| ≡ 10&lt;sup&gt;−13&lt;/sup&gt; s
| = 100 fs
|-
| [[week]] || wk
| ≡ 7 d
| = {{nowrap|604 800}} s
|-
| [[year]] (Gregorian) || a, y, ''or'' yr
| = 365.2425 d average, calculated from common years (365 d) plus leap years (366 d) on most years divisible by 4. See [[leap year]] for details.
| = {{nowrap|31 556 952}} s
|-
| year (Julian) || a, y, ''or'' yr
| = 365.25 d average, calculated from common years (365 d) plus one leap year (366 d) every four years
| = {{nowrap|31 557 600}} s
|-
| [[sidereal year|year]] (sidereal) || a, y, ''or'' yr
| ≡ time taken for Sun to return to the same position with respect to the stars of the celestial sphere
| ≈ {{nowrap|365.256 363}} d ≈ {{nowrap|31 558 149.7632}} s
|-
| [[tropical year|year]] (tropical) || a, y, ''or'' yr
| ≡ Length of time it takes for the Sun to return to the same position in the cycle of seasons
| ≈ {{nowrap|365.242 190}} d ≈ {{nowrap|31 556 925}} s
|-
|COLSPAN=&quot;4&quot;|Where [[UTC]] is observed, the length of time units longer than 1 s may increase or decrease by 1 s if a [[leap second]] occurs during the time interval of interest.
|}

