| ≡ One unit rpm equals one rotation completed around a fixed axis in one minute of time.
| ≈ {{val|0.104719755|u=rad/s}}
|}

===Speed or velocity===
{| class=&quot;wikitable&quot;
|+ [[Speed]]
!Name of unit
!Symbol
!Definition
!Relation to SI units
|-
| [[foot (length)|foot]] per [[hour]] || fph
| ≡ 1&amp;nbsp;ft/h
| ≈ {{nowrap|8.466 667{{e|−5}}}} m/s
|-
| [[foot (length)|foot]] per [[minute]] || fpm
| ≡ 1&amp;nbsp;ft/min
| = 5.08{{e|−3}} m/s
|-
| [[foot (length)|foot]] per [[second]] || fps
| ≡ 1&amp;nbsp;ft/s
| = 3.048{{e|−1}} m/s
|-
| [[furlong]] per [[fortnight]] || &amp;nbsp;
| ≡ furlong/fortnight
| ≈ {{nowrap|1.663 095{{e|−4}}}} m/s
|-
| [[inch]] per [[minute]] || ipm
| ≡ 1 in/min
| ≈ {{nowrap|4.23 333{{e|−4}}}} m/s
|-
| [[inch]] per [[second]] || ips
| ≡ 1 in/s
| = 2.54{{e|−2}} m/s
|-
| [[kilometre per hour]] || km/h
| ≡ 1&amp;nbsp;km/h
| ≈ {{nowrap|2.777 778{{e|−1}}}} m/s
|-
| [[knot (speed)|knot]] || kn
| ≡ 1 [[nautical mile|NM]]/h = 1.852&amp;nbsp;km/h
| ≈ {{nowrap|0.514 444}} m/s
|-
| [[knot (speed)|knot]] (Admiralty) || kn
| ≡ 1 NM (Adm)/h = {{nowrap|1.853 184}} km/h {{Citation needed|date=September 2008}}
| = {{nowrap|0.514 77{{overline|3}}}} m/s
|-
| [[mach number]] || ''M''
| Ratio of the speed to the speed of sound in the medium. Varies especially with temperature. About 1225&amp;nbsp;km/h (761&amp;nbsp;mph) in air at sea level to about 1062&amp;nbsp;km/h (660&amp;nbsp;mph) at jet altitudes. Unitless
| ≈ 340 to 295&amp;nbsp;m/s for aircraft
|- style=&quot;background:#dfd;&quot;
| [[metre per second]] (SI unit)|| m/s
| ≡ 1&amp;nbsp;m/s
| = 1&amp;nbsp;m/s
|-
| [[mile per hour]] || mph
| ≡ 1&amp;nbsp;mi/h
| = {{nowrap|0.447 04}} m/s
|-
| [[mile]] per [[minute]] || mpm
| ≡ 1&amp;nbsp;mi/min
| = 26.8224&amp;nbsp;m/s
|-
| [[mile]] per [[second]] || mps
| ≡ 1&amp;nbsp;mi/s
| = {{nowrap|1 609.344}} m/s
|-
| [[speed of light]] in vacuum || ''c''
| ≡ {{nowrap|299 792 458}} m/s
| = {{nowrap|299 792 458}} m/s
|-
| [[speed of sound]] in air || ''s''
| Varies especially with temperature. About 1225&amp;nbsp;km/h (761&amp;nbsp;mph) in air at sea level to about 1062&amp;nbsp;km/h (660&amp;nbsp;mph) at jet altitudes.
| ≈ 340 to 295&amp;nbsp;m/s at aircraft altitudes
|}
A [[velocity]] consists of a speed combined with a direction; the speed part of the velocity takes units of speed.

