| ≡ m&lt;sub&gt;e&lt;/sub&gt;·[[fine structure constant|α]]&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;·''[[speed of light|c]]''&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;/[[Bohr radius|a&lt;sub&gt;0&lt;/sub&gt;]]
| ≈ {{nowrap|8.238 722 06{{e|−8}}}} N &lt;ref&gt;[http://physics.nist.gov/cuu/Constants/ ''CODATA Value: atomic unit of force'']. (2006). [[National Institute of Standards and Technology]]. Retrieved September 14, 2008.&lt;/ref&gt;
|-
| [[dyne]] ([[cgs unit]]) || dyn
| ≡ g·cm/s&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;
| = 10&lt;sup&gt;−5&lt;/sup&gt; N
|-
| [[kilogram-force]]; kilopond; [[grave (mass)|grave]]-force || kgf; kp; Gf
| ≡ ''g'' × 1&amp;nbsp;kg
| = {{nowrap|9.806 65}} N
|-
| [[kip (unit)|kip]]; kip-force || kip; kipf; klbf
| ≡ ''g'' × 1 000&amp;nbsp;lb
| = {{nowrap|4.448 221 615 2605{{e|3}}}} N
|-
| [[grave (mass)|milligrave]]-force, gravet-force || mGf; gf
| ≡ ''[[standard gravity|''g'']]'' × 1 g
| = {{nowrap|9.806 65}} mN
|- style=&quot;background:#dfd;&quot;
| [[newton (unit)|newton]] (SI unit) || N
| A force capable of giving a mass of one kg an acceleration of one metre per second, per second.&lt;ref name=cipm1946&gt;{{citation | title=[[Comité International des Poids et Mesures]], Resolution 2 | url=http://www.bipm.org/en/CIPM/db/1946/2/ | year=1946 | accessdate=August 26, 2009}}&lt;/ref&gt;
| = 1&amp;nbsp;N = 1&amp;nbsp;kg·m/s&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;
|-
| [[ounce-force]] || ozf
| ≡ ''g'' × 1 oz
| = {{nowrap|0.278 013 850 953 7812}} N
|-
| [[pound-force|pound]] || lb
| ≡ slug·ft/s&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;
| = {{nowrap|4.448 230 531}} N
|-
| [[pound-force]] || [[lbf]]
| ≡ ''g'' × 1&amp;nbsp;lb
| = {{nowrap|4.448 221 615 2605}} N
|-
| [[poundal]] || pdl
| ≡ 1&amp;nbsp;lb·ft/s&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;
| = {{nowrap|0.138 254 954 376}} N
|-
| sthene ([[Metre-tonne-second system of units|mts]] unit) || sn
| ≡ 1 t·m/s&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;
| = 1{{e|3}} N
|-
| [[ton]]-force || tnf
| ≡ ''g'' × 1 sh tn
| = {{nowrap|8.896 443 230 521{{e|3}}}} N
|}
