Please note that although becquerel (Bq) and hertz (Hz) both ultimately refer to the same SI base unit (s&lt;sup&gt;−1&lt;/sup&gt;), Hz is used only for periodic phenomena, and Bq is only used for stochastic processes associated with radioactivity.&lt;ref name=sibrochure222&gt;{{citation | url=http://www.bipm.org/en/si/si_brochure/chapter2/2-2/table3.html | title=The International System of Units, Section 2.2.2., Table 3 | edition=8 | publisher=[[Bureau International des Poids et Mesures]] | year=2006 | accessdate=August 27, 2009}}&lt;/ref&gt;

